      "metric": "Average email open rate",
      "value": "22.86%",
      "source_url": "https://example.com/report",
      "confidence": "high"
    }
  ]
  ```

  ## Confidence Levels
  - **high**: From reputable industry reports (Gartner, Forrester, HubSpot, etc.)
  - **medium**: From blogs, case studies, or secondary sources
  - **low**: Estimated or from non-authoritative sources

  ## Rules
  - Always cite the source URL
  - Include confidence level for each metric
  - Prioritize recent data (current year or previous year)
  - Return at least 3 metrics when possible
  - Note the date/year of the data when available
